spectraxai.spectraxai.SpectralPreprocess.doc:
Spectral Preprocessing enum

A collection of different spectral pre-processing (or pre-treatments) that may be applied to a spectral matrix.
Initialize a SpectralPreprocessing object from its string representation

spectraxai.spectraxai.Spectra.doc:
Spectra class to hold a 2-D spectral matrix.

Can accept a 1-D vector but always returns a 2-D matrix.

spectraxai.spectraxai.Spectra.sg.doc:
Apply a general Savitzky–Golay transform.

You need to pass as kwargs the parameters of scipy.signal.savgol_filter

spectraxai.spectraxai.Scale.doc: Scaling of an input feature (or of the output) supported by the Dataset class

spectraxai.spectraxai.DatasetSplit.doc: Types of dataset split supported by the Dataset class

spectraxai.spectraxai.Dataset.doc:
A general class to manage the dataset (i.e. X and Y).

Use this class to pass your 2D spectral matrix and 1D or 2D output properties. Supports methods for pre-processing X, scaling X and Y, splitting the dataset, and more.
